llmsInstallationContent:
ZeroMind is an MCP plugin that drives a 3D engine running in the user's browser. Install via Cline's MCP Servers UI (Command Palette → "Cline: MCP Servers" → "Configure MCP Servers"):
```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "zeromind": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@origozero/zeromind"],
      "env": { "ZEROMIND_IDE_NAME": "cline" },
      "disabled": false,
      "autoApprove": []
    }
  }
}
```
Then drop the agent rule:
```
npx @origozero/zeromind install cline
```
Or write `.clinerules/zeromind.md` yourself with the content of https://raw.githubusercontent.com/OrigoZero/zeromind-plugin/main/templates/manual.md

First engine-related prompt triggers a one-time device-code link at https://origozero.ai/link.
